headline: Realtor.com® Rent Report: More Renters Looking to Relocate Outside Their City
summary: Rents edged down in October, marking the 27th straight month of year-over-year declines and the third consecutive month-over-month dip, according to the Realtor.com® October Rental Report. Meanwhile, the makeup of renters in many markets is shifting – compared with before the pandemic, 20 of the 50 largest metros have transitioned from mostly local renter activity to greater demand from out-of-market shoppers.
